Update: I added debug borders (blue for .message.user, red for .loading). Fresh page test shows the OPPOSITE problem now - the loading indicator (red border) is WIDER than the user message!

Looking at the CSS:
- .message has: width: 90%, max-width: 90% (NO flex property)  
- .loading has: flex: 0 0 90%, width: 90%, max-width: 90%
- .chat-container has: display: flex, flex-direction: column, align-items: flex-start
- .message.user has: align-self: flex-end

So the loading with flex: 0 0 90% is now wider than the message without it. Should I add flex: 0 0 90% to .message as well? Or is there a better unified approach?
